se></svg></div></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hip1665702803864.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hip1665702803864.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hip1665702803864.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hip1665702803864\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Implementation type defined or available for the component.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hip1665702803864__p_d6278e1_d6279e1_d6280e1\">A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the non-Uniface implementations.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hip1665702803864__p_d6281e1_d6282e1_d6283e1\">A component can have the following implementations:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Component Implementations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\">Implementation type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\">Operations available by default</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\">Editable</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\">Comments</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\"> Uniface Component </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"> Y </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\"> These are built-in Uniface operations. You can\n                     define parameters for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code> operation only. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\"> These are explicit operations. If you define\n                     operations named <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code>  and <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>  they are\n                     activated implicitly. For more information on <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code>  and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code> see <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">operation</span>. <p class=\"p\">You cannot\n                        define parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\"> C </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\">You can define the default operations\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code> , and <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>\n                     and the implicit operations <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.\n                        <p class=\"p\">You cannot define parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>,\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> or\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">However, if you define both 4GL and C implementations for a component, the\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>\n                        parameters become available. If you then delete the 4GL implementation,\n                        these parameters remain available for the C implementation.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\"> COM </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\"> Java Call-in </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\"> Stored Procedure </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__1\"> Operating System Service </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMAND</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMANDOUT</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hip1665702803864__table_d557e1_d558e1_d559e1__entry__4\"> Enter operating system commands using\n\t\t\t\t ProcScript to be executed via an Operating System Service. You can use your assignment file to\n\t\t\t\t redirect the Operating System Service components to a Uniface server. <p class=\"p\">The maximum length of a command is 511\n\t\t\t\t bytes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hip1665702803864__section_dg3_h3f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d735884e292\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"hip1665702803864__ul_x5l_h3f_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hip1665702803864__li_d3113e1_d3114e1_d3115e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ird1665702714456.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ird1665702714456.html\" title=\"A Signature is a Development Object that describes the remote interface of a component, or modeled entity operation. Signatures for Uniface components and modeled entity operations are automatically generated, but signatures for non-Uniface components that Uniface can call at runtime, must be explicitly defined.\">Signature</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420250\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8420250\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Version: Use up/down arrow keys to navigate, Esc to collapse. Rocket Uniface Library 10.4 Reflection Desktop Benutzerhandbuch V17.0 Reflection FTP Scripting Guide (Deutsch) V17.1 Reflection Desktop Benutzerhandbuch V17.1 Reflection FTP Scripting Guide (Deutsch) V17.0 Reflection Desktop User Guide (German) Secure Host Access FTP Client User Guide (German) Reflection FTP Command Reference (German) V21.0 Reflection FTP Client User Guide (German) V21.0 Reflection FTP Client User Guide (German) V21.1 Reflection FTP Scripting (German) V21.1 Reflection FTP Command Reference (German) V21.1 Rocket Uniface Library 10.4 Rocket Uniface Library 10.4 Reflection Desktop Benutzerhandbuch V17.0 Reflection FTP Scripting Guide (Deutsch) V17.1 Reflection Desktop Benutzerhandbuch V17.1 Reflection FTP Scripting Guide (Deutsch) V17.0 Reflection Desktop User Guide (German) Secure Host Access FTP Client User Guide (German) Reflection FTP Command Reference (German) V21.0 Reflection FTP Client User Guide (German) V21.0 Reflection FTP Client User Guide (German) V21.1 Reflection FTP Scripting (German) V21.1 Reflection FTP Command Reference (German) V21.1 Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Type Implementation type defined or available for the component. A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the non-Uniface implementations. A component can have the following implementations: Table 1. Component Implementations Implementation type Operations available by default Editable Comments Uniface Component ACCEPT , EXEC , QUIT Y These are built-in Uniface operations. You can define parameters for the EXEC operation only. INIT , CLEANUP These are explicit operations. If you define operations named INIT and CLEANUP they are activated implicitly. For more information on INIT and CLEANUP see operation . You cannot define parameters for INIT and CLEANUP . C None N You can define the default operations ACCEPT , QUIT , and EXEC and the implicit operations INIT and CLEANUP . You cannot define parameters for ACCEPT , QUIT , INIT or CLEANUP . However, if you define both 4GL and C implementations for a component, the ACCEPT , QUIT , and EXEC parameters become available. If you then delete the 4GL implementation, these parameters remain available for the C implementation. COM None N No default operations are available. Java Call-in None N No default operations are available. Stored Procedure None N No default operations are available. Operating System Service COMMAND , COMMANDOUT N Enter operating system commands using ProcScript to be executed via an Operating System Service. You can use your assignment file to redirect the Operating System Service components to a Uniface server. The maximum length of a command is 511 bytes. Applies To Signature Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}